The paper discusses a privacy concern related to smartphone sensing and data collection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed mechanism, PinMe, utilizes both non-sensory and sensory data stored on the smartphone, as well as publicly-available auxiliary information, which suggests the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of social and information retrieval (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), multimedia (cs.MM), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
